# Results

This section presents the results of our empirical study on the LiaScript ecosystem, structured around our five primary research questions (RQs). Each subsection corresponds to a specific RQ and its associated sub-questions, providing detailed analyses and findings derived from our comprehensive dataset of LiaScript courses.

## RQ1: Adoption and Scope

*How large and diverse is the LiaScript ecosystem?*

### RQ1.1: Ecosystem Scope

*What is the overall size of the LiaScript corpus in terms of courses, repositories, and contributors?*

This section presents the findings from our comprehensive analysis of {{ results.descriptive_stats.corpus.total_courses | default(2751) | large }} validated LiaScript courses, organized by research question.

First of all, we would like to highlight the overall growth of the LiaScript ecosystem over time. Figure 1 presents the cumulative development of the LiaScript ecosystem from 2018 to 2025, showing both the number of courses and the number of contributors (committers) over time.

![Cumulative development of LiaScript courses and users (2018-2025)](../figures/fig_cumulative_growth.png){width=80%}

The data reveals exponential growth patterns for both metrics. Starting from a small base in 2018, the ecosystem has grown to encompass over 2,500 courses created by approximately 300 contributors by the end of 2025. Notably, the growth accelerated significantly in 2025, with 64% of all investigated courses created in that year alone—representing a 288% increase compared to 2024.

### RQ1.2: Thematic Distribution

*What is the thematic distribution across academic disciplines?*

