The Dewey Decimal Classification (DDC) is a widely used library classification system that organizes knowledge into ten main classes, each identified by a three-digit number. Using AI-assisted classification (LLM-based), we categorized courses into DDC top-level categories to provide an overview of dominant disciplines:

